Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Surveillance and espionage in the Cold War
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydql3
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 3 Apr 1987
The case of US marine Clayton Lonetree accused of espionage in Moscow reminds Cooke of how electronic surveillance was feared at the founding of the UN in 1945.